President Joseph R. Biden Jr. spoke with Crown Prince Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan to reaffirm the partnership between the United States and the United Arab Emirates. They discussed various collaborations on space, climate, defense, and security. They also talked about regional and global challenges such as Afghanistan, the threat posed by Iran, and the quest for peace in the Middle East. President Biden emphasized the strategic importance of the normalization of relations between the UAE and Israel and expressed support for strengthening and expanding these arrangements. They also agreed to work together on addressing conflicts, including the humanitarian crisis in the Tigray region of Ethiopia.